parts.text: I have created the
database schema for the **IBE160 AI CV & Job Application Assistant**.

Here is a summary of the tables I created:

1.  **`profiles

`**: Stores user profile information (full name, avatar, etc.), linked to their Supabase Auth account.
2.  **`cvs`**:

Stores uploaded CVs, including extracted text content and the file path in storage.
3.  **`job_descriptions`**: Stores job descriptions that users want to analyze

.
4.  **`analyses`**: Links a specific CV to a specific Job Description and stores the AI-generated analysis (score, feedback).

I have also enabled **Row Level Security (RLS)** on all tables to
ensure users can only access their own data. A trigger was added to automatically create a user profile when a new user signs up.
